===Faculty===
ASU faculty have included former [[CNN]] host [[Aaron Brown]], [[meta-analysis]] developer [[Gene V. Glass]], and [[Pulitzer Prize]] winner and ''[[The Ants]]'' author [[Bert Hölldobler]]. [[Donald Johanson]], who discovered the 3.18 million year old fossil hominid [[Lucy (Australopithecus)]] in Ethiopia, is also a professor at ASU, as well as [[George Poste]], Chief Scientist for the [[Complex Adaptive Systems Initiative]]. [[Nobel laureate]] faculty include [[Leland Hartwell]],&lt;ref&gt;[http://asunews.asu.edu/20090908_hartwell Nobel Prize in Physiology or Medicine ASU News Release] 09/08/09&lt;/ref&gt; [[Edward C. Prescott]], and [[Elinor Ostrom]].{{fact|date=May 2011}}

==Notes==
{{Cnote|a|Campus emrollment figures at ASU are defined by the number of students taking at least one course offered by a department housed on a particular campus. Students who are enrolled in classes on more than one campus (estimated to be 13,269) are counted within each campus's total.}}

{{Cnote|b|ASU is the largest research university in the US under a single administration (one President, Provost, VPs, etc.). In addition ASU's Tempe campus is the [[List of United States university campuses by enrollment|largest single university campus]] in the US.}}

