==Sister cities==
Astoria has one [[sister city]],&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.sister-cities.org/icrc/directory/usa/OR Sister Cities International&lt;!-- Bot generated title --&gt;]&lt;/ref&gt; as designated by [[Sister Cities International]]:

*{{flagicon|Germany}} [[Walldorf]], Germany, which is the birthplace of Astoria's namesake, [[John Jacob Astor]], who was born in Walldorf near Heidelberg on July 17, 1763. The sistercityship was founded on Astor's 200. birthday on July 17, 1963 in Walldorf by Walldorf's mayor Wilhelm Willinger and Astoria's mayor Harry Steinbock.&lt;ref&gt;{{cite book|last=Ebeling|first=Herbert C.|title=Johann Jakob Astor, Walldorf Astor-Stiftung|year=1998|isbn=3000037497|pages=351–354}}&lt;/ref&gt;

