      <text xml:space="preserve">{{Wiktionary|aquila}}
'''Aquila''' is the Italian word for ''eagle'' and may also refer to:
* [[Aquila (constellation)]], the astronomical constellation The Eagle
* [[Aquila (genus)|''Aquila'' (genus)]], a genus of birds including some eagles
* [[Aquila (journal)]], an ornithological journal
* [[Aquila (Roman)|''Aquila'' (Roman)]], a Roman military standard
* [[Priscilla and Aquila|''Aquila'' (of Priscilla and Aquila)]]. They were a prominent New Testament couple who assisted Paul of Tarsus

==Places==
* [[L'Aquila]], sometimes Aquila, a town in Italy
* [[Aquila, Michoacán]], town in Michoacán, Mexico
* [[Aquila, Veracruz]], municipality in Veracruz, Mexico
* [[Aquila, Switzerland]], former municipality in the canton of Ticino in Switzerland

==People==
* Aquila, a [[Naples|Neapolitan]] surname
* [[Priscilla and Aquila]], a Biblical person from the Acts and Paul's letters
* [[Aquila of Sinope]], second-century translator of the Old Testament
* [[Frank Aquila]], a Manitoba judge
* [[Frank J. Aquila]], an American lawyer
* [[Alberto Aquilani]], Italian footballer

==Entertainment and literature==
* A book by [[Andrew Norriss]]
* [[Aquila (TV series)|''Aquila'' (TV series)]], a BBC TV production for children based on the Norriss book
* A [[Ace Combat 04: Shattered Skies#Music List|song in the video game ''Ace Combat 04: Shattered Skies'']].  In supplemental materials, the official designation of the enemy Yellow Squadron is Aquila Squadron.
* A game server in the MMORPG [[MapleStory]]
* [[Aquila (children's magazine)]], a children's magazine
* Captain Crowe Almedio's ship in the video game [[Star Ocean: The Last Hope]]

==Vehicles==

* [[USS Aquila (AK-47)|USS ''Aquila'' (AK-47)]], an Aquila-class cargo ship commissioned by the U.S. Navy for service in World War II.
* [[USS Aquila (PHM-4)|USS ''Aquila'' (PHM-4)]], a hydrofoil formerly operated by the U.S. Navy
* [[Italian aircraft carrier Aquila|Italian aircraft carrier ''Aquila'']], a World War II Italian aircraft carrier
* The Lockheed [[MQM-105 Aquila]], the U.S. Army's first UAV for reconnaissance
* Hyosung Aquila: a series of cruiser motorcycles made by [[Hyosung Motors &amp; Machinery Inc.]]
* &quot;[[The Aquila]]&quot; Coachbuild futuristic car based on the [[Austin Maxi]].Styled by Chris Field after winning competiiton, organised by the [[Daily Telegraph]] and the Institute of British Coachbuilders and Motor Manufactures in 1972
* [[Aquila AT01]], a light weight training aircraft built in Germany

==Organisations==
* [[Aquila Airways]], a British flying boat operator (1948&amp;ndash;1958)
* [[Aquila, Inc.]], a former electric and gas utility in Kansas City, Missouri, United States
* [[Aquila Italiana]] Italian car manufacturer or brand

==Warhammer 40,000 universe==
* The aquila is the symbol of the [[Imperium (Warhammer 40,000)]] in the fictional Warhammer 40,000 universe
* [[Equipment of the Imperium (Warhammer 40,000)#Power_armour|Aquila pattern power armour]] is the most commonly used type of power armour in the Space Marines inventory
* The [[Vehicles of the Imperium (Warhammer 40,000)#Aquila Lander|Aquila Lander]] is a light shuttle used by the Imperial Navy

